Overview 
Tonal is looking for an experienced senior manager to drive initiatives that will dramatically improve the service and reduce the cost of our Logistics operations. The role will build a team of experienced leaders in continuous improvement, analytics, logistics technology, and project management. Your team will initiate and oversee projects to improve organization capabilities. You will also be responsible for ongoing continuous improvement and Lean initiatives across the logistics organization. You will drive the analytics that uncover and define opportunities for improvement, including inventory deployment, installation capacity and network design among other areas. You will work in close partnership with leaders in Logistics as well as business leaders, IT development and other stakeholders. 
What You Will Do 
Develop and manage the Logistics Strategic Plan as part of the Operations overall Strategic Plan. Ensure all internal and external Logistics resources are aligned and execute to the strategic plan; Identify, define, and pursue opportunities for improvement in customer experience, service, and cost across our warehousing, delivery, and installation operations. Build a top-notch team to drive analytics, continuous improvement, technology innovation and project management. Improve logistics performance whilst collaborating closely with other functional leaders across the business. Responsible for managing those projects on budget, on time and on benefit; Represents and lead the Logistics efforts as part of broader Entreprise or Operations efforts (eg. MIDAS, Planning,...) Lead identification, selection and implementation of new technology platforms (for example, TMS, Dispatch and Scheduling). Oversee ongoing improvements in our logistics technologies. Drive continuous improvement in service levels, cost, quality, safety. Help achieve year-over-year improvement in key performance metrics. Be a change agent: challenge organizational leaders to drive continuous improvement. Initiate and oversee organization training and development in Lean kaizen, 5S and Value Stream mapping. Partner effectively across functional teams, including Logistics and Field Operations, Customer Care, Manufacturing Operations and multiple 3PL service providers, to drive projects from ideation to execution 
Who You Are 
An experienced logistics and supply chain leader with a minimum of 7-10 years experience. A data driven leader with impressive analytical capabilities An expert in tools such as Lean Kaizen, 5S, Value Stream Mapping, process Flow Mapping, and overall company culture changes. Experience with selection and deployment of technology in logistics operations. Comfortable with a fast paced, innovative and entrepreneurial environment. Able to create a roadmap for success 
